76561198270925363,Not Recommended,269030,20166491,"Posted: 31 December, 2015",all,kharygalt19,"This game looked hilarious but would have been better as a card-/boardgame with friends. The concept as a PC game felt spectacularly lackluster and took about 12 minutes to complete from start to finish. You choose up to 4 characters and rotate between them, choosing a different map location for them to perform Task A or B. It has stats that change each turn you make and you're given Result X or Y for each turn. (That's it. Choose a location, choose an action, event happens, you choose your response, solution. End of turn. This whole process takes about 30 seconds max) Overall the game would have been much cooler as anything other than a pc game. If you're easily amused by ""Well that escalated quickly!"" type scenarios, you'll love it. Otherwise I'm annoyed I paid money for this game, even at half off."
