,Not Recommended,269030,12983750,"Posted: 17 November, 2014",all,Tartrazine,"boring and simplistic, even if you like the genreThis is sold as a rich Choose Your Own Adventure style game, like King of Dragon Pass. It's actually a very short raising sim where you have six turns to beef up your characters (don't stress about which characters to pick - they're functionally identical, *ONLY* their art is different) before a disaster affects the city. Before playing, I somehow had the idea that the Yawhg disaster was different every playthrough. It's not! It's always the same, you can't protect anyone from it, and (despite all the other weird magic stuff in the game) the nature of the disaster is really boring. After the disaster is over, you choose your new post-Yawhg career and succeed or fail (to varying degrees) based on your stat points and sometimes the special events you experienced. (Note that the careers have no stat requirements, because programming in a ""Given that you have literally zero Charm, the other survivors laugh at your suggestion that you should be the leader"" message would have been too much work).A single playthrough lasts about 10-15 minutes. You can play again and get new events and endings, but I started seeing repeats as early as mysecondplaythrough, so no thanks."
