,Recommended,269030,9748655,"Posted: 6 April, 2014",all,FLFL KoiKois,"The Yawhg is a game of stories, stories that the player travels through randomly, forever hoping that they will survive the eponymous disaster.I shall not beat around the bush here. The gameplay in The Yawhg is incredibly minimal, with the only real player input being what actions the characters take during the six week ingame cycle. The game instead focuses heavily on the story and world interactions your choices create.The in depth details in The Yawhg are astounding with many in-game events big and small, hidden in obscure event pathways, based entirely on the skills you have bult up for your characters.But because of skill and day limitations it may become extremely tiresome for many players to try and see some of the Yawhgs more inner secrets, as they may accidentally trigger a event to occur earlier than they wished, or even a different event than what is wished for to occur.The main thing to keep in mind though when purchasing this game is this: Do you have any friends who live near you?If yes then The Yawhg is a great game to play as its couch co-op focus can make for a fun and eventful time. If not and you also have no means of streaming events to friends and playing that way, you will find yourself playing a game for four on your ownsome, and as fun as the game can be, playing it by yourself can be a very tiresome experience.Basically buy this game if you like fun storytelling and have friends."
