76561198054093290,Recommended,269030,12448634,"Posted: 11 October, 2014",all,Ebenezer,"I have played a fair bit of The Yawhg and I for one love it though i can see why some people would dislike it. The Yawhg is basically a game were up to 4 people (locally)pick a character and go to a location where you choose an action you would like to do for example pickpocketing. When you do the action some of your stats will increase. As well as you doing the action and getting stats for that you will also have a random encounter for example finding some lost townsfolk. These random encounters can decrease or increase your stats. After you choosing six locations in turns (one for every week) the Yawhg will come. After the Yawhg comes and the town is destroyed you have to choose a role such as builder how well you perform these roles will be affected by your stats. After everyone in the game has picked there role and told how well they did at it you will be told if you saved the town and shouldnt have any more issues with the Yawhg(good ending),survived(neutral ending) or if the town stays in ruin's(bad ending). Surprisingly in my opinion the more unique cool ending's(for your character) come if you get the bad ending for the town.All in all The Yawhg is a fun game to play with friends. It has a unique art style and its replay value is very big because of the countless endings and random encounters. I think it is well worth its price especially if it is in a sale."
