,Not Recommended,269030,13648791,"Posted: 27 December, 2014",all,Smol Complaining Bat,"This game in and of itself is fun. Sure, some things get a little repetitive since there's only so many dialogue options once things get rolling, but the game itself is fine. What I was not aware of, however, was that this game is in a fixed resolution and sound quality. What does that mean?? You can't change the resolution and you can't lower or raise the sound. And this is actually a big deal.One of the main draws of the game is using locations around the town to better your stats and wealth before the Yawhg comes. Sounds pretty easy, just have to make some tough decisions. Which is fine. It's good. Except that depending on your monitor, you can't see your base or upgraded stats. And that causes kinks when you actually progress past Week 6, and things get a little more interesting.While over all the lack of different resolutions is mostly cosmetic, it is something to consider and think about before purchasing this game. And if I had known that there weren't any resolution options before I bought it, I wouldn't have spent my money on it."
