,Recommended,269030,10672205,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,Detective Ken,"Made over a space of three months for a game jam and subsequently put up for sale when it proved popular and is in fact a finished game.In this choose your own adventure, you play as 4 characters, either all at the same time or whatever you want, buddy! Bring a friend or 2 and you can be the dude and them the 2 chicks and you can just party for 6 weeks in the pub!Ultimately this game is about knowing the apocalypse will come and choosing how you spend your remaining days; Effectively changing the end of your character, not so much the town or people in it.I'm sure I'm incredibly bias because Emily Carroll is my favorite artist/writer combo, but her signature style is very present in the... grimmer parts of the story, and I never thought there'd be music that compliments it all so well. Anyway, it's very offbeat yet classic fantasy, but well designed and like all of Emily's work, short-lived but worth going back to later.So if you want a short, beautiful, uncomplicated experience you can get through while you're waiting for your hair to dry, or for your favourite show to download, or dinner to cook, then look no further."
