76561197999539552,Recommended,269030,9572331,"Posted: 20 March, 2014",all,Tomn,"A very good party game that's great for developing emergent stories - like the tale of a humble woodcutter who became known for punching fists until they broke, gave to charity, and fought crime, the story of a simple man who kept getting♥♥♥♥♥♥on by life and ended up giving much of his wealth to help his city before living out an entirely ordinary life, or the gadabout socialite who made a million friends and got absolutely nowhere at the end of her life, becoming a drunk instead of contributing to society.It does NOT really work as a single player game, however.  You really need at least one other player for the game to truly take off, and it works best with a full set.  The joy comes out of everyone's choices and motivations and goals bouncing off everyone else's and providing contrast - puppetmastering everyone for some kind of optimal result just isn't that interesting.  Shame it's local multiplayer only, then, but given how complex netcode can be, it's understandable.In short, get this game if you can drag at least one friend in to play with you in real life.  Otherwise, it's much more hit-or-miss."
