,Recommended,269030,10507794,"Posted: 17 June, 2014",all,Nilesy @ Twitch,"The Yawhg is a choice-based adventure where you must select a character and await the arrival of the deadly Yawhg.I played a little over 80 minutes, and thoroughly enjoyed the game. First, let's discuss it's strengths.The Yawhg is beautiful. The artwork is all fantastic and fits the theme of the game perfectly. The music and soundtrack of the game is haunting and wonderful. The gameplay is interesting and, at first, exciting. The story is enjoyable and satisfying.And now, the negative sides of the game. It's short. Not such a bad thing, but when coupled with the retail price, the sense of worth is a little low. I got 80 minutes of gameplay out of the game, which I did enjoy, though the price is a little high for my taste.  Next up, again, the gameplay. After one or two playthroughs of the game, the mechanics are no longer exciting as you can kind of see what's happening quite easily, meaning completion of the game can be easily ""gamed"" (if you know what I mean). The game also lacks achievements. Woah woah wait, that's not a bad thing right? Actually, I think in this case, it is. Achievements mean nothing, it's true, but I think, had The Yawhg had achievements, it would have added a heck of a lot more replayability as the achievements could direct your play, asking you to complete sub-stories, professions, and multiple side ideas which, after completion, many will not revisit.Either way, a really charming and lovely game. I enjoyed it thoroughly.Nilesy"
