,Recommended,269030,9294125,"Posted: 28 February, 2014",all,Bubba the Hutt,"While rich in story and offering many different stories to be told for up to 4 players, Yawhg still seems to fall short of the game that it could have potentially been. The game is essentially for 1-4 players, each taking their turn of where to go during the week, what to do at said location, and how you respond to a random event. This process lasts for several weeks, around 6 or 8 I believe, before the ""Yawhg"" comes. After the Yawhg comes, the game sums up your ending randomly. While fun, witty, and comedic, the ""adventure"" that players go through is drastically short and is merely based on week to week events rather than the accumulative story. For $9.99 I would say the game is extremely short (lasting around 5-15 minutes depending on how fast you can read) and I would recommend it as a nice steam summer sale pick up. Other positive notes include pretty artwork, interesting scenarios, and a short-lived entertaining adventure game. I would give it a 5 out of 10."
