,Recommended,269030,11042880,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,SoiledWig,"As far as setting a mood through music, storytelling, pacing, the logic of choices and consequences, and the juxtaposition of looming disaster to the characters' blythely going about their lives, the game is simultaneously funny, poignant and a little chilling. In short, this game hits all the right notes in attempting what it aims to do. It's short enough that you can get through the whole thing in one sitting and immediately want to do it all over again to try different scenarios; it's also just long enough that it feels as though what you decide has some impact on the world and you can even see some far-reaching, unexpected consequences down the line. It's deceptively complex, and brilliant in its simplicity."
