,Recommended,269030,11018278,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,This Puny Human,"For those who enjoy board games, the Yawhg feels familiar. Averything happen in turns and random events, shaping your character's evolution and leading to their sucess or failure at the conclusion.Things to keep in mind if you want to buy this game:1- It's really short. Really, really short. Takes about 7 turns to finish one gameplay.Then you get the conclusion and can start again. Since events are random, you'll probably find new things when playing for the second (and third, fourth, etc) time, but things start to repeat soon.2- It's best if played with friends. Not online, but at your side, using the same computer. You can have up to four players and I could only have real fun with The Yawhg after I invited others to play with me. Like I said before, very similar to a board game.With that in mind, chances are you won't be surprised and will end up having fun. The visuals and songs are really well done too. It's not worth a lot of money and I think would be best as a Ipad game, but it's a nice idea. Not for everyone, though. Makes me wish they would release an expansion, with more events, locations, etc. As it is now, I fear is way too short and might get repetitive too soon. Still, I had fun, and that's what counts."
