76561198063522393,Recommended,269030,9301180,"Posted: 1 March, 2014",all,flickjovany,"I wish the game had more substance but the art and writing keep it from blending into other games like this. First off, no online co op mode, which is weird to want but this would have been perfect for my friends and I to play over skype. The game gives you four characters to choose from, all very unique and different. You have six weeks before this ""Yawhg"" decends onto the world. Each turn you get to choose where your character decides to spend their week. Once you make a choice you then choose between two paths and two paths again, you get text for what your character does within these branching paths but this is the formula it sticks with. You gain (or lose) stats depending on your decisions. Once the six weeks are up the Yawhg appears and you have some choices after it does appear. At this point your characters stats and your own choice determine whether the characters and towns fate is positive or negative.For the price I can't complain, I really need to try some of the other paths. It's definitely unique and something you won't get all too often."
