,Recommended,269030,12163111,"Posted: 20 September, 2014",all,GameDragonZero,"The Yawhg is, let's be honest, an experiment in creating a multiplayer version of those raise-stat type story games.  This doesn't mean it's bad - it's quite good - but know what you're getting into when you buy it.  Basically it's a smart visual novel game for parties.Two to four characters make choices, lead lives, and prepare as a strange threat - the Yawhg - approaches.  Doing things raises character stats and affects other elements of the game.  A magical experiment, a won gladiatorial event, an undifused bomb, all affect other characters.  When the disaster does happen, characters then choose their path after, which affects the end of the game.Gameplay is pretty short - the game is meant to be replayed.  Graphics are decent, and the storybook look really works.  Music is great.So the question on buying it is ""do you want an experimental multiplayer story game.""  If you do, this is for you.  Otherwise, its not for you - but I consider it a good game."
