76561198117493929,Recommended,269030,17923497,"Posted: 6 September, 2015",all,Mayumi Sato,"I really can't express well enough my love for this game, how good it is or how impressed I still am at its rejogability. I honestly never found a game focused on the story that had a level this high of rejogability and story based games are my favorite ones! I played this game dozens and dozens and dozens of times with my auntie, my cousin and my sister - sometimes other guests but mostly them - and I saw dozens and dozens and dozens of variations of events and endings to the point of thinking ocasionally that I finally had found everything that had to be found there but I always had the pleasant surprise of discovering that I was very mistaken. To this day, I still don't doubt that there things I didn't saw in that game even though I played it A LOT(my hours may indicate that).The Yawgh is a mostly story based game but its drawings have a beautiful style with lovely colours and together with its soundtrack, they create the perfect atmosphere for the tale of the seven days of some townies before the Yawgh comes to destroy it.Btw, there's NOTHING you can to stop the Yaghw of coming. This is one of the points in which the story starts to differ of the classical RPGs we all know. Your objective is to obtain points in certain habilities by going to places with random events during every week until everything is destroyed and you can finally put your talents in a good use(or not, there's a bad and a medium ending after all!).Each event is written very well and there's A LOT of them and EVEN MORE variations of it according to not only your habilities but also some events that might happened during others players turns! The random events of this game sometimes get connections and form a little story line, which is freaking awesome. If you poisoned the water in week 02, there's a great chance that you and your friends will see some consequences of it in different locations during the rest of the game. In some cases, the random events can even affect directly your ending!Another wonderful, AWESOME thing about this game is the fact that there's not only the ""Town's ending"" - that can be great, medium or bad - but there's also a individual ending to each player based on their actions during the game, how they contributed to the rebuilding of the town and also how much the city recovered. If you get a great town ending, you may get a happy and amazing ending! If you don't, believe me, things can get a extremely dark turn.The only thing that is sad is the fact that we can't play it in online multiplayer mode but oh well. This is a great game to play alone and with local friends!This is one of the best games that I ever played and I still hold it in my heart(and play everytime I meet someone who doesn't know it).10/10!"
