,Recommended,269030,12669991,"Posted: 28 October, 2014",all,Jamesy,"The Yawhg is more of a choose-your-own visual novel than a game - Designed for four players, the game excels most in having a mood and a feeling. The visuals are quaint and a little cutesy, as is the music which stands as its own thing. The gameplay is incredibly simple, just having you choose where to go on a map, and what activity to do there. You're then ushered through an event which results in a decision which will affect the stats your character builds, and over the few turns your character will grow and be left with a final choice.The Yawhg never feels disappointing or like you've failed to experience a story, despite its very short playthrough length. It leaves you with a good ending that is based on what you did in the the days before the return of The Yawhg.On the whole I would recommend this to people who are interested in that kind of concept - Tabletop RPG players who might have a quick playthrough with a couple of friends. It feels more tabletop than it does videogame."
