,Recommended,269030,29815087,Posted: 9 February,all,TieKuhn,"The Yawhgis one of those games where you can see great potential for a party setting. When brought into a party setting however, you find plenty of room for laughs all around as each person(or groups of people if you decide to have characters run democratically) encounters the day to day life before encountering the Yawhg. The unpredictable nature of when certain scenarios will occur, and the probability of having correct scores when these great events arise allow for experimentation with each playthrough. The games taking about 20 minutes, this gives the game great versatility in the party setting. I truly recommend this game to anyone who is often looked to as the bringer of party games during grand rendevous, and those who find games that require multiple ways of thinking quite intriguing. So step into the adventure as blue, red, yellow, or green as you prepare for the coming of the Yawhg."
