,Recommended,269030,34391597,Posted: 21 August,all,MangaEngel,"While playable alone, ALWAYS play this with friends. Play it online or locally, doesn't matter.It is a multiplayer where only one copy is needed, so buy it and enjoy a fun little storytime with your friends.Graphics:Beautiful handdrawn images, always with small variations depending on which character is currently active.Music:Calm and non-distracting, perfect to allow one (or multiple) player to read the story out loud.Gameplay:It is simple and yet amazing. Up to four players live in town and can choose one of various locations where a random event will play. Each event allows two possible reactions which may or may not lead to a longer story down the road. Does the event work out or fail? Your stats will define your success which can be raised by visiting certain places and doing certain actions.And when the Yawgh has come, will you help to save the town or lead it to it's doom for selfish reasons?According to the creators, it takes about 120 hours to see EVERY event, so be ready for a lot of fun sessions!Other:The game is as dark as it is funny.Have a sex orgy with orcs, destroy a hospital as a werewolf, win a singing contest or drink the wine of the king. Would you rather drink a burning potion or simply swing it out the window? And when a ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ offers you a nice evening, will you go with her or leave her to her own devices?But be aware, your choices can matter more than you think and you might find the town being overrun by rampant monster plants or find yourself becoming an addicted drunk in the sewers."
,Recommended,269030,34382791,Posted: 20 August,all,furiouscuddles,"Love this game, immense replay value!"
